figcaption%3EThis%20photo%20from%20May%2021%2C%202025%2C%20shows%20a%20new%20facility%20with%20a%20perimeter%20and%20guardhouse.%3Cp%3EPlanet%20Labs%20PBC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20May%2021%2C%202025%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20a%20new%20facility%20with%20additional%20security%20had%20been%20built%20in%20the%20northern%20corner%20of%20the%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20they've%20done%20is%20they've%20put%20a%20perimeter%20up%20that%20consists%20of%20three%20layers%20of%20fencing%2C%20and%20the%20middle%20layer%20is%20more%20enhanced%2C%26quot%3B%20Kristensen%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20entrance%20at%20the%20southern%20corner%20of%20the%20facility%20is%20covered%2C%20likely%20for%20guards%20to%20inspect%20trucks%20while%20out%20of%20sight%20from%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thermonuclear%20warheads%20stored%20at%20such%20sites%20would%20likely%20be%20tactical%20nukes%2C%20which%20are%20more%20portable%20and%20create%20vastly%20smaller%20explosions%20and%20fallout.%20A%20single%20warhead%20would%20be%20roughly%20the%20size%20of%20a%20small%20oven%20and%20weigh%20about%20450%20to%20650%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20special%20unit%20is%20typically%20tasked%20with%20transporting%20these%20warheads%2C%20whether%20via%20helicopter%20to%20be%20fitted%20onto%20a%20missile%20or%20by%20truck%20to%20a%20storage%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKristensen%20also%20identified%20a%20covered%20off-loading%20ramp%20among%20a%20cluster%20of%20trees%2C%20which%20likely%20leads%20to%20a%20bunker%20for%20warhead%20storage.%20On%20the%20eastern%20side%20of%20the%20compound%2C%20a%20massive%20orange%20antenna%20for%20command%20and%20control%20can%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20security%20measures%20are%20the%20tell-tale%20signs%20of%20Russian%20nuclear%20sites%20that%20experts%20watch%20for%20in%20satellite%20imagery.%20Particular%20care%20has%20to%20be%20given%20to%20these%20warheads%20not%20only%20for%20their%20strategic%20impor