3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20lengthy%20six-hour%20interview%20with%20podcaster%20Lex%20Fridman%20published%20Saturday%2C%20the%20exec%20shared%20the%20two%20key%20things%20he%20looks%20for%20when%20hiring%20new%20computer%20programmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUp%20until%20this%20point%2C%20the%20main%20pivot%20point%20for%20getting%20hired%20was%20not%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20was%20not%20the%20schooling%20you've%20had%2C%20it%20was%20not%20your%20grades%2C%20it%20was%20not%20your%20pedigree%2C%26quot%3B%20Hansson%2C%20who%20is%20also%20known%20as%20DHH%2C%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20AI%20could%20now%20change%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20about%20how%20well%20you%20do%20two%20things%3A%20your%20cover%20letter%20and%20your%20programming%20ability%2C%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20only%20work%20with%20people%20remotely%20if%20they're%20good%20writers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Fridman.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can't%20pen%20a%20proper%20cover%20letter%20and%20can't%20bother%20to%20put%20in%20the%20effort%20to%20write%20it%20specifically%20for%20us%2C%20you're%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20you%20had%20to%20be%20able%20to%20program%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20the%20degree%20that%20I%20can%20look%20at%20your%20code%20and%20go%20like%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20I%20want%20to%20work%20with%20that%20person.'%20Not%20only%20do%20I%20want%20to%20work%20with%20that%20person%2C%20I%20want%20to%20work%20on%20that%20person's%20code%20when%20I%20have%20to%20see%20it%20again%20in%20five%20years%20to%20fix%20some%20damn%20bug.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHansson%20said%20that%20applicants%20would%20have%20to%20show%20their%20skills%20through%20a%20programming%20test%20that%20%26quot%3Bsimulates%20the%20way%20we%20work%20for%20real.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20surprised%20time%20and%20again%20where%20I%20thought%20for%20sure%20this%20candidate%20is%20a%20shoo-in%2C%20they%20sound%20just%20right%2C%20the%20CV%20is%20just%20right%2C%20and%20then%20you%20see%20the%20code%20getting%20turned%20in%20and%20I'm%20like%2C%20'No%20way.%20No%20way%20are%20we%20hiring%20this%20person%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20capacity%20to%20evaluate%20work%20product%20is%20a%20superpower%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20hiring.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWriting%20cover%20letters%20has%20long%20been%20a%20necessary%20evil%20for%20job%20candidates.%20Often%20regarded%20as%20time-consuming%20and%20repetitive%2C%20many%20are%20also%20put%20off%20by%20rumors%20that%20hiring%20managers%20simply%20don't%20read%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20for%20jobs%20that%20don't%20specifically%20ask%20for%20one%2C%20studies%20suggest%20cover%20letters%20are%20still%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20application%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20a%20Resume%20Genius%20survey%20of%20625%20hiring%20managers%20across%20the%20US%20found%20that%2083%25%20said%20they%20frequently%20or%20always%20read%20cover%20letters.%20And%2073%25%20of%20managers%20at%20companies%20that%20did%20not%20require%20cover%20letters%20also%20said%20they%20frequently%20read%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20applicants%20to%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-write-cover-letter-different-industries-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20key%20to%20a%20successful%20cover%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20conveying%20experience%20with%20relevant%20technology%20and%20providing%20a%20snapshot%20of%20what%20you'd%20bring%20to%20the%20specific%20company%2C%20Thomas%20Vick%2C%20a%20senior%20regional%20director%20at%20the%20talent%20firm%20Robert%20Half%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20return%20on%20investment%20have%20you%20created%20for%20an%20organization%3F%26quot%3B%20Vick%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20have%20you%20done%20in%20your%20career%20that%20has%20helped%20save%20a%20company%20time%2C%20energy%2C%20and%20money%3F%26quot%3B%