w-to-grow-avocado-in-india-urban-farmer-harshit-godha-imports-saplings-from-israel-teaches-farming%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavocados%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0called%20Arka%20Supreme.%20This%20variety%20caught%20his%20attention%20because%20it%20could%20adapt%20to%20Maharashtra%E2%80%99s%20hot%20climate%2C%20thriving%20even%20in%20temperatures%20as%20high%20as%2040%20to%2045%20degrees%20Celsius%20%E2%80%94%20perfect%20for%20Beed%E2%80%99s%20environment.%20%E2%80%9CArka%20Supreme%20is%20a%20high-yielding%20variety%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20it%20would%20work%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%20confidently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20quest%20for%20knowledge%2C%20Parmeshwar%20visited%20the%20ICAR-Indian%20Institute%20of%20Horticultural%20Research%20(IIHR)%20in%20Bengaluru%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20avocado%20cultivation.%20There%2C%20he%20acquired%20valuable%20insights%20into%20farming%20practices.%20Equipped%20with%20this%20newfound%20knowledge%2C%20he%20ordered%2050%20avocado%20saplings%20from%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-74-1752147602.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22No%20one%20in%20Beed%20believed%20that%20avocado%20farming%20could%20succeed%2C%20but%20Parmeshwar%E2%80%99s%20perseverance%20paid%20off%20in%202021%20when%20his%2050%20plants%20began%20to%20produce%20fruit!%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-74-1752147602.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-74-1752147602-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-74-1752147602-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEAT